The national chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Comrade Adams Oshiomhole, says President Muhammadu Buhari deserves good elected lieutenants to continue the development of the country towards greater height. Oshiomhole disclosed thison Thursday in Lafia while presenting the party’s flag to the APC gubernatorial candidate in Nasarawa state, Engr. Audu Sule, and his deputy, Dr. Emmanuel Agabe. “The sixteen wasteful years of Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) is being remedied in three years by the taming of corruption and bad international image of the country due to PDP’s bad governance,” he said. According to him, the international community among others have been praising the change agenda of President Muhammadu Buhari for turning around the country from negative to positive limelight. In his remarks, the former governor of Nasarawa state, Abdullahi Adamu, said President Muhammadu Buhari needs assistance from the electorate to vote APC candidates in all elections for him to continue developing the country without saboteurs. In his speech, Governor Umaru Tanko Al-Makura said, “APC in Nasarawa state is a united family and solidly behind President Muhammadu Buhari and the national chairman, Adams Oshiomhole. However, the governorship candidate, Engr. Sule assured that President Buhari would win Nasarawa state in 2019. He further pledged to bring in foreign investors to develop the state, if elected. We''ll not shortchange you or allow anybody to – Buhari We won’t short-change anybody — Buhari Buhari leads APC campaign, harps on continuity